<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Knee-Push-Up">Knee Push-Up</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/knee-push-up" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">knee push-up</a> is a regression of the traditional push-up, great for beginners looking to improve their upper body strength. The intensity is decreased, so the lifter can gradually increase their strength to progress to the traditional variation. </p>



<p>It activates muscle groups like the serratus anterior, pectorals, and triceps, all while <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27693098/#:~:text=The%20isolated%20protraction%20of%20the%20shoulder%20girdle%20in%20a%20kneeling%20position%20is%20as%20sufficient%20as%20the%20push%2Dup%20plus%20in%20activating%20the%20SA%20selectively.%20Therefore%2C%20we%20recommended%20this%20exercise%20for%20clients%20who%20are%20unable%20to%20perform%20an%20entire%20push%2Dup%20or%20should%20avoid%20detrimental%20stress%20on%20the%20shoulder%20joint." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">decreasing stress on the shoulder joint.</a> Beginners can take advantage of this calisthenics exercise to improve their fitness without equipment or going to the gym. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="32111201-Kneeling-Push-up-(male)_Chest" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/982355635?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Knee Push-Up Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Start in a tabletop position on your hands and knees.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Adjust your hand position slightly forward.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Slightly lean the torso forward until your body is aligned from head to knees. This is your starting position.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Preserve a neutral spine position throughout the exercise.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Inhale and bend at the elbows to lower the chest to the floor.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Pause at the bottom.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Exhale and push through the hands to return to the starting position.</li>



<li>Repeat for goal-driven sets and reps.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Maintain a straight back in the knee push-up. Allow the hips to move forward to create a straight line from head to knees.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Put a towel or roll up a mat to make a cushion for your knees.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



